class Solution {
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        int[] dp = new int[nums.length];
        dp[nums.length - 1] = 1;
        int ans = 1;
        for (int i = nums.length - 2; i >= 0 ; i--){
            int max = 1;
            for (int j = i + 1; j < nums.length; j++){
                if (nums[i] < nums[j]){
                    if (max < 1 + dp[j]){
                        max = 1 + dp[j];
                    }
                }
            }
            dp[i] = max;
            if (max > ans){
                ans = max;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

/*
Notes:

(Using “Dynamic Programming”.)

Value functions of Q300: 
  dp[ i ] = max( dp[ j ] + 1 ), 其中0≤j<i且num[j]<num[i]
  ans = max( dp[ i ] ), 其中0≤i<n

Explanation: 
  The current dp value equals to 1 add the maximum of all the available dp.
  The available dp means the indexes in the range of [current index + 1, arr.length - 1] and arr[current index] < arr[indexes in the range].

*”Boundary condition”: 
  1. Setting the dp value of last index to 1.
  2. Start from the last index of the list instead of the first index.
  3. Meeting the requirements mentioned in the “Explanation”.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cjWnW0hdF1Y
*/
